  "prompt": "Why did Marco Arment sell Instapaper?",
  "response": "Marco Arment, the creator of Instapaper, sold the app for several reasons. One primary reason was the challenge of scaling the business and managing its growth. Running a rapidly growing app involves a lot of operational, technical, and administrative complexities, which can be difficult for a small team or solo entrepreneur to handle.\n\nIn addition, Arment wanted to focus on new projects and opportunities. By selling Instapaper, he could free up time and resources to pursue other interests and ventures. He found a suitable buyer in Betaworks, a company that showed interest in continuing to develop Instapaper and expand its user base.\n\nOverall, the sale was driven by the desire to ensure the long-term success and growth of Instapaper while also allowing Arment to advance his personal and professional goals.",
